AU  - Kohlhagen, Steven W.
PY  - 1978
DA  - 1978/06/01
TI  - A Model of Optimal Foreign Exchange Hedging Without Exchange Rate Projections
JO  - Journal of International Business Studies
SP  - 9
EP  - 19
VL  - 9
IS  - 2
AB  - This article presents a technique for optimal hedging decisions for a general set of international financial problems, specifically within the context of a floating exchange rate regime. The techniques discussed are designed specifically to require neither exchange rate projections nor the specification of a utility function for the decision-maker. Rather, the decision-maker is encouraged to analyze the implications of a given financial strategy over a reasonable range of future exchange rates, choosing the strategy that best meets corporate financial goals in light of possible (and uncertain) exchange rate fluctuations.
